bug.short_desc: SEVERE: An OutOfMemory error happened while running the report.

long_desc.thetext:
Build ID: M20060118-1600
Steps To Reproduce: 1.download birt runtime 2.2.1 2.deploy in my webserver tomcat 3.create a report and run it through my application 4.it cause the error "org.eclipse.birt.report.engine.api.impl.RunTask doRun SEVERE: An OutOfMemory error happened while running the report."
More information:
can you attach the report design?

how many rows in the dataset used for CHART? It seems there are too many rows in the CHART.
re-assign to CHART team for deeper investigate.

If you create a table instead of chart with the same data, does it still fail?
Can you send us some data to reproduce the issue?

With the attached report, I removed chart and created a script data set, the data set has 100 thousand rows, it still fail. it shows the issue is not in chart side. nkpsu, how many rows in your data set used for the report?
Thanks.

I tested several cases with 5k, 10k, 50k ,100k rows and against default JVM heap size and custom JVM heap size of tomcat5.5.23, my custom JVM heap parameters are '-Xms64m -Xmx512m'.Also I used JProbe7.01 to watch the memory leak.
The Result shows there is no memory leak, after report generation and rendering, the remained BIRT class only are some model/metadata objects, I think maybe these objects were hold by current session and their total size only has 153,264 Bytes. When I used default JVM heap setting to preview chart report, only 5K rows can be previewed correctly, other's rows threw OutOfMemeory exception. When I changed JVM heap setting to '-Xms64m -Xmx512m', the preview is correct for all rows cases. And Chart limits the max rows in source code, if row number is greater than 10k, chart will ignore.
Nkpsu, I guess maybe your report contains huge rows, if then, I suggest you should change your default JVM heap setting, to increase the heap memory. And I also suggest you use the new 2.3 version of BIRT, it has been support DtE integration, now the grouping/sorting of chart will be done by DtE, it means the rows data has been grouped/sorted by DtE before it passed to chart, so it will reduce memory usage and computing time for chart when there are plenty of rows.
